00:09:16,329 --> 00:09:17,370
about people in Hong Kong

283
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:18,630
when I was there last year

284
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:20,720
and especially in 2014

285
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,320
during the Umbrella Movement,

286
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,000
was their genuine love of Hong Kong

287
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,490
that drove them to resist the CCP's

288
00:09:26,490 --> 00:09:28,720
encroachment on their way of life.

289
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,399
And it has made a difference.

290
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:32,540
If Hong Kongers hadn't stood up against the
CCP

291
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:33,959
in the last 20 years,

292
00:09:33,959 --> 00:09:35,089
the CCP would have imposed

293
00:09:35,089 --> 00:09:36,329
an anti-subversion law

294
00:09:36,329 --> 00:09:39,180
that would ruin Hong Kong's freedoms,

295
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:41,310
patriotically re-educated their kids,

296
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:43,120
and given them the formality of

297
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:45,190
"universal suffrage" without a real vote.

298
00:09:45,190 --> 00:09:46,350
So yes,

299
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:47,370
the future of Hong Kong

300
00:09:47,370 --> 00:09:49,170
does depend on what happens in

301
00:09:49,170 --> 00:09:51,580
the Party's internal power struggle.

302
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:54,600
But it also depends on the people of Hong
Kong,

303
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:57,360
and whether they continue to resist the Party.

304
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,000
Because one thing's clear:

305
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
the Chinese Communist Party

306
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,839
won't stop trying to control Hong Kong.

307
00:10:02,839 --> 00:10:04,680
And for those of us outside Hong Kong,

308
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,350
the last 20 years is a warning.

309
00:10:06,350 --> 00:10:09,040
A warning to Taiwan about what reunification

310
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,399
with a China controlled by the CCP

